&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THERAPIES DIRECTORATE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Greenmead Special School&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 HIGHLY SPECIALIST OCCUPATIONAL THERAPIST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term Opportunity (Maternity Cover) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Fixed Term Band 7 Occupational Therapist Maternity Cover within Greenmead Special School. The post holder will work within a dynamic, multidisciplinary team to provide integrated therapy to children aged 2-11 years old with a wide range of diagnoses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will allow successful applicants to further develop their clinical reasoning and treatment skills with this diverse population, with additional opportunity for service development as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you have a minimum of 4 years post-registration experience, with knowledge of special schools an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for supervising Band 6 Occupational Therapists and/or Therapy Assistants, and participating actively in the multi-disciplinary team meetings, including working with education and care staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are strongly committed to evidence based practice and have a robust multi-disciplinary working ethos in place to support staff with their continuing professional and personal development as well as service development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barbara Coward, Clinical Team Lead barbaracoward@stgeorges.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0208 789 1466&lt;/p&gt;
